				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There's no "standard" convention to pattern table layout.  It depends on what size and shape (square, rectangular, or irregular) of meta-sprite you're using, how complex your animations are, and of course on what hardware sprite size (8x8 or 8x16) you're using.  If you look at five different commercial games you'll probably find five completely different implementations, and quite likely multiple methods in the same game (e.g. in a platformer like Ninja Gaiden, powerup items and small enemies could be simple 2x2 tile squares while the player and larger enemies could be irregularly-shaped)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

